<subSubSection id="00043D7029E7260A7FA22891801E5377" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" type="identification">
<paragraph id="F497AE3D3765E19FD363FD1A4862C922" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE4B4E45A0153EE62AF1967519DCCCF5" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Test medium sized (test diameter = 28 mm); round and robust. Marginal series with regular and small tubercles. Interambulacra with distinctively large, crenulate primary tubercles. Areoles slightly deepened. Apical system covered with tubercles, ocular plates exsert. Periproct raised, with plates decreasing in size inwards. Primary spines cylindrical, tapering gently. Oral spines broad, flattened, slightly curved, with serrated edges. Secondary spines flattened, narrowing towards blunt point. Primary spines brown to purplish violet, with white shaft. Secondary spines light brown. Denuded test white.</paragraph>
<caption id="B3FF6C2BB16F134888022A97B58CC8E2" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
<paragraph id="EFCAE41C615694AA17EA6AA1478EFCE6" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
