<normalizedToken id="9B6E38517E1B823761566877CFBA620D" originalValue="A–B">A-B</normalizedToken>
(SAMC.A090123, off Mossel Bay): 
<taxonomicName id="E2398F106838FB518560BCB89E56BB22" class="Echinoidea" family="Histocidaridae" genus="Histocidaris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Histocidaris purpurata" order="Cidaroida" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="purpurata">Histocidaris purpurata</taxonomicName>
. A Aboral view of preserved specimen with partially removed spines B Oral view of preserved specimen with partially removed spines 
<normalizedToken id="AA726953ACB7F9D252D5D4879ACBD6E1" originalValue="C–D">C-D</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="2CBB2844C8FA44C54F31598735B5C4FB" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echinothrix diadema" order="Diadematoida" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="diadema">Echinothrix diadema</taxonomicName>
C (RMCA.2561, Ispingo). Aboral view of partially denuded test D (RMCA.2568, Sodwana Bay). Oral view of preserved specimen with spines 
<normalizedToken id="8AD7915473D36064E394F9AC6368FD1A" originalValue="E–F">E-F</normalizedToken>
(SAMC.A090124, Sowdana Bay): 
<taxonomicName id="580BEA92AC69EEBC1ABFE0E5BFD24396" class="Echinoidea" family="Temnopleuridae" genus="Microcyphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microcyphus rousseaui" order="Camarodonta" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rousseaui">Microcyphus rousseaui</taxonomicName>
E Oral view of preserved specimen with spines F Aboral view of preserved specimen with spines 
<normalizedToken id="B9F3B4761326BF845DE6AD3462FB1932" originalValue="G–H">G-H</normalizedToken>
(SAMC.A090126, Park Rynie): 
<taxonomicName id="537742F8E4AC68E1784066FD19731306" class="Echinoidea" family="Toxopneustidae" genus="Pseudoboletia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudoboletia maculata" order="Camarodonta" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="maculata">Pseudoboletia maculata</taxonomicName>
G Aboral view of preserved specimen with spines H Aboral view of preserved denuded test. Scale bars: 2 cm (A, B, G, H); 1 cm (
<normalizedToken id="ACB3AC5EB7D2A5471664573700785171" originalValue="C–F">C-F</normalizedToken>
). All images were edited in GIMP 2.8.22 by Dr Carl Palmer and plate created by Zoleka Filander.
</paragraph>
